16/11/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia renewed its offer of a reward of 1m euros for information leading to the arrest of war crimes fugitive Ratko Mladic. "Anyone who gives us valid information leading to Mladic's arrest will get 1m euros," Serbia's chief liaison to The Hague war crimes tribunal (ICTY), Rasim Ljajic, told the daily Vecernje Novosti on Friday (November 14th). The National Security Council has also announced a 250,000-euro reward for the other remaining Hague fugitive, Goran Hadzic. (Vecernje novosti, B92, Reuters, Makfax - 14/11/08)
